<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="4afeebc98ed2862af3edb7afa9a30d08" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/heroclix/treports/treports.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/vs/treports/treports.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/treports/treports.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Reflections Release Toronto, May 16<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=14267'>Michael "T_Mac" Ium</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=14267&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 17, 2004</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Hmm here&#39;s another TR from me, continuing my streak of doing TR&#39;s when I do well and I&#39;m bored the next day. This Reflections release event was going to be just a Standard tourney, with Reflections being legal. We were all supposed to get a Sauron AI card, but apparently he was held up at the border (wonder how Sauron liked that cavity search). <br />
<br />
I was planning on playing Elf/Man with a bunch of the new cards, but unfortunately I didn&#39;t pull Elendil, Narsil, Isildur, or Boromir for me to try out. So instead of going with plain ole Frodo, I went with the hot new thing, GIMLI as my ring-bearer, with Arwen and GLORFINDEL as my starting companions (their strength is crazy wow). To raise Gimli&#39;s resistance (and to use another of my new cards) i put in a Ring of Fury, and Gimli&#39;s buddy Thrarin. As my final secret dwarf tech, i added Here lies Balin, Son of Fundin (HLBSOF!!!) <br />
<br />
For my shadow I still wanted to play threat Nazgul, but Glorfindel was scaring me, so I added 3 Black breaths and a Blade tip. Away we go...<br />
<br />
Round 1- John Ellis (New style Dauntless/Threat nazgul)<br />
<br />
John&#39;s dauntless was really interesting, because he started Glorfindel and the 2 hobbits, and played 4 Legolas&#39; in his draw deck. Oddly, he was using Frodo but still chose to bid 0, as did I. He won the odd/even game, and went first. He played DH, and some random tales (he was using Pippin, Friend to Frodo HA) and moved to 2, where I played a Witch King with pale blade, but his shire tales couldnt be discarded!!! Guess the joke&#39;s on me. On my turn I played Aragorn and some other stuff, and moved to 2, where he played 2 nazgul. One was overwhelmed by Glorfindel, and I doubled to 3, taking wounds. The game really started to get interesting at site 5, when John overwhelmed TWO of my nazgul with Glorfindel in 1 turn......yipes. I was maxed out on threats (Captured by the ring/Fat one wants it)at site 6, when he played Bill Ferny and assigned to Gimli. Since I couldn&#39;t add 2 threats, i had to add 2 burdens. I moved to site 7 where he played....Bill Ferny. I was hoping he&#39;d play another minion so i could sack Thrarin to remove the threats, but John knew what he was doing. I had to add another 2 burdens. At site 8 he played......yup Bill ferny! I had the ring of fury on, so my resistance was 7. Two more burdens at site 8 got me to 6! Glorfindel, Aragorn, and Arwen were all really bored at this point. Before I moved to 9 time was called, and he asked me if I could stop Bill ferny one more time. I showed him Greenleaf in my hand, and he conceeded. Whew close one!<br />
<br />
FW<br />
Wow Glorfindel overwhelmed 3 nazgul all game what a beast. Ferny almost won it for him, he was playing Four!<br />
<br />
Game 2- Miguel Bernardo (FIghting chicks, Morgul archery)<br />
<br />
Games against Miguel are always fun, and he usually has an original deck to play. He bids 2 to go first, and starts Arwen, Eowyn and Frodo, for which I heckle him for not using a new Ring bearer. He simbelmynes for Eomer and moves, i drop 1 nazgul which makes him stop. I double past him to 3, since his orcs don&#39;t really get going until site 4. Miguel singles into 3. When I move into 4, Miguel plays Streaming to the field, and 3 of the Orcs that add 2 archery when he has initiative. Before taking even a single nano-second to think about it, with a smug grin I play Secret Sentinels to ditch Streaming to the field and Fat one wants it. Then I look at my hand...I ONLY HAVE THREE CARDS LEFT OMG A;LDSFASLDJFAS;DFJ. Miguel has a good laugh at my expense, especially since I had Elrond/Vilya out and i could have just bounced Streaming to the field instead! So instead of taking 0 archery, i take SIX! I stop, and Miguel gets Eomer tanked out, along with a Thundering host. He moves to 4, where I play some random minions and he decides to stop. Moving to 5 I&#39;m a little worried, but relieved when he plays only 2 minions, neither of which add to the archery total. I think it was a Morgul skulker to shuffle 2 minions back into his deck, and Gollum. Since site 5 is huge for his deck and there was no reason not to play guys there I decide to double, and he plays nothing. He moves to site 5, where I play a WK with pale blade and Cantea. Cantea ditches Firefoot, and Miguel forgets to discard my pale blade with arrow-slits :) The Witch King wreaks some major havoc, killing off Eomer (Miguel thought he would win with Thundering host). At site 6 Miguel shows me his hand of 8 fellowship cards, and conceeds :<br />
<br />
FW- Miguels draws were pretty bad, Witchking with pale blade woo! OMFG that move at site 4 with secret sentinels was horrible<br />
<br />
Round 3- Josh Corny-head Moe (DH, Besiegers)<br />
<br />
Well it&#39;s always a tough game when you gotta play Josh. He won the toss to go first, and started DH, Pippin WOBAS, Merry FTS and BOROMIR WOOHOO! He played Aragorn and moved to 2, where I was able to drop a black breath and my only blade tip. He didnt want to get those on Aragorn so he stopped. I played Aragorn and some toys and doubled to 3. Josh played Elrond, which made me a little nervous, but moving to 3 I played a nazgul against Josh which he was forced to block with Aragorn, getting him breathed and tipped. He stopped. At site 3 i was still looking for Derufin or Elrond, so I added 1 threat with the site and drew a shadow card. I&#39;m not sure what i was doing, he had Their Marching companies out, and a site controlled. One threat was enough (too much?) and I moved. He played a troll and another dude which I blocked. At the start of Josh&#39;s turn I looked at Aragorn and saw a wound, and figured he had taken blade tip already...he hadn&#39;t : So I forgot to make him wound him :( Moving to 4 I played Toldea, and with 3 twilight left discarded Elrond with Fear, woohoo Aragorns not getting healed up yet. He stopped. Moving to 5 I was able to play Elrond and Derufin, and discarded Encirclement and an engine with Secret Sentinels. In regroup I discarded 3 more engines with Derufin (hes such a pimp). I had a good shadow hand so i stopped. I made him wound Aragorn with blade tip (2 to go!) and he moved, I think he lost Pippin here, and was forced to use Merry and block. He also blocked with Aragorn, so he&#39;d die next turn if i remembered :O I moved to 6 and ditched more engines, and he singled to 6 losing Aragorn. I moved to 7 in good shape, but his fellowship was down to Legolas and Boromir so I stopped. For his fellowship he played Sam, and someone else and moved. Sam and the someone else died and he stopped. He pulled a nice move here by pumping Boromir with Merry to get him to 13 strength and discarded the nazgul he beat. I moved to 8 and he played nothing, but with Aragorn with 2 wounds and Thrarin out I wussed out and stopped. I was afraid he&#39;d play the guy that made all besiegers fierce, and i was pretty sure i could kill him if he doubled. He had exhausted Legolas with Splendor and Elven rope, and healed Boromir with 4 Gondor bowmen out. He moved to 8 giving me 11 twilight and i played nothing, and he promptly doubled to 9. I played Witch King, Enquea, and Cantea, and he played Might of Numenor, which made me panic for a second. Unfortunately for him he could only give me 10 archery, and I had 11 vitality. The last nazgul would kill Legolas, threats would go off, and when Boromir had to fight he&#39;d kill or corrupt himself :) Whew close one!<br />
<br />
FW- Wins against Josh are always a feather in the cap, Boromir in DH is NICE! He also played Elven rope, which is so tech against swarms, gollum, grima, bill ferny, etc.<br />
<br />
Round 4- John Prada (Rohan/Gandalf/Sauron corruption)<br />
<br />
John won the bid and went first. He simblemined for Eomer and played Theoden and moved, where I played Bill ferny, WK with Pale blade, and Otsea. Jeez thats 2 games in a row where i&#39;ve gotten God draws at site 2 against John :) Eowyn blocked Otsea twice and Theoden died to the WK, calling up Hrethel to sacrifice himself for Rohan as well. I doubled to 3, and was able to keep myself ahead all game with Elrond/Vilya bouncing Desperate defense all game, or discarding it with Secret sentinels. When I needed someone else to fight, Gimli just blocked. There wasn&#39;t anything he could do, I finished with 0 burdens. <br />
<br />
FW- Games like these make me glad im not playing Rohan anymore, Elrond/secret sentinels is so good. God draw at site 2 w00t<br />
<br />
Round 5- Mike Nykoluk (HIDAN/threat nazgul)<br />
<br />
He started Eomer, Eowyn, and Boromir :) He went first and played Aragorn, Eowyn&#39;s sword and a Rider&#39;s mount, giving me enough pool for Attea and sword to go nuts. He had to sacrifice Eowyn here. For my site 2 I also flooded the pool with Aragorn, Greenleaf and Elrond. He played Attea as well, along with the Orc thats fierce/dmg+1 while spotting a nazgul. I shot Attea twice, and assigned him to Glorfindel. The twilight cost of the card on top of my draw deck would be huge, either the Orc becomes toothless and Attea dies and I easily double, or I take some major damage. I slowly lift the top card and reveal.......VILYA!!!!! aldsjfla;sdjf<br />
So Legolas dies and i take major wounds and stop. Mike moves to 3, and makes a joke that he gave me enough for a WK, Pale blade, and black steed. I say thats exactly what I have, and hes like &quot;haha yeah right!&quot; Unfortunately for him I wasn&#39;t joking :) His freshly played Elendil (and his incredible vitality for HIDAN) is canceled when hes overwhelmed. I move to 3 without incident. He moves to 4 where I play Attea, and I also have black breath/blade tip out. He&#39;s forced to exhaust Aragorn to shoot him down. At site 4 I had a chance to overwhelm 1 of the 2 nazgul he played, but decided I didn&#39;t want to move ahead so I just blocked and stopped. At site 5 he played Hrethel, which finally allowed him to simbelmyne for Eomer&#39;s toys. Unfortunately for him Cantea just ditched them :) At site 5 he lost Eomer and stopped. I moved to 5 and took some wounds. He moved to 6 and I played Otsea, who was 9 to Aragorn&#39;s 10, until he exerted from Brego and became an 11 :) Aragorn died here. I moved to 6 but was going for the shadow kill and stopped. He moved to 7 with Sam, Derufin, Hrethel and Boromir with a black breath. Unfortunately time was called here, and after Sam died he was left with an exhausted Derufin, exhausted Hrethel and Boromir with 3 wounds. He was one site ahead, and took the timed win. I was really frustrated cuz i thought the game was in the bag, but the time limit ran out. <br />
<br />
Timed loss- Stupid time limit, well after SOS i still ended up #1, so im getting a Sauron t-shirt tommorow woohoo! We had a good turnout for the release, 24 ppl, good time was had by all, reflections cards rock! Reflections distribution and cost blow :( <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=5015&view=1&PHPSESSID=4afeebc98ed2862af3edb7afa9a30d08'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?PHPSESSID=4afeebc98ed2862af3edb7afa9a30d08'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=4afeebc98ed2862af3edb7afa9a30d08'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
